  "original_title": "\u0ba4\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bc6\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Private bus services continue to suffer",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "Private bus services continue to suffer due to ongoing tension in the country and shortage of diesel.",
        "Due to this, only 10 percent of the buses were put into service on Thursday, the 14th, said Kemunu Wijeratne, President of Sri Lanka Private Bus Owners Association.",
        "Meanwhile, it has been reported that about 3,000 buses of Sri Lanka Transport Board have been put into service yesterday.",
        "5000 buses will be put into service by the Sri Lanka Transport Board on normal days. However, Sri Lanka Transport Board has informed that only about 3000 buses have been put into service on the 14th due to the decrease in the number of passengers and employees.",
        "The Railway Department had informed that the trains would run as usual yesterday afternoon. The Railway Department mentioned that the train was running as usual.",
        "Meanwhile, it is noteworthy that the curfew was enforced at 12 noon on the 14th in Colombo and public transport services were limited and people were facing various problems in going to their homes."
      ],
